Pygmalion, a famous Statuary‚ provoked by the dissolute Lives of the Pro- poetides, throws off all Fondness for the Sex, and resolves on a perpetual Celibacy. But afterwards, falling in Love with a Statue he had made, Venus, at his request, animates it ; upon which he marries his newly-in- spired Mistress, and has a Son by her, who afterwards built the City of Paphos, which bears the name of its Founder.
